ex.enText: Our national strength has increased since 1982.

synonyms.bx: 通常指体力或人、事物等拥有的实力。

tr: the property of being physically or mentally strong
capacity to produce strong physiological or chemical effects

example: he hit with all the force he could muster
it was destroyed by the strength of the gale
a government has not the vitality and forcefulness of a living man

tr: permanence by virtue of the power to resist stress or force
example: they advertised the durability of their products

tr: the amount of energy transmitted (as by acoustic or electromagnetic radiation)
example: he adjusted the intensity of the sound
they measured the station's signal strength

tr: an asset of special worth or utility
the power to induce the taking of a course of action or the embracing of a point of view by means of argument or entreaty
example: the strength of his argument settled the matter

tr: capability in terms of personnel and materiel that affect the capacity to fight a war
example: we faced an army of great strength
politicians have neglected our military posture
the strength of the company's stock in recent weeks

value.def: Your strength is the physical energy that you have, which gives you the ability to perform various actions, such as lifting or moving things.

example.ex: She has always been encouraged to swim to build up the strength of her muscles...
example.tran: 一直有人鼓励她去游泳以强健体魄。

example.ex: He threw it forward with all his strength...
example.tran: 他使尽全力把它扔向前方。

example.ex: You don't need strength to take part in this sport...
example.tran: 参加这项运动不需要太多体力。

example.ex: He leant against the wall, fighting for strength to continue.
example.tran: 他靠在墙上，努力想鼓起劲继续下去。

value.def: Someone's strength in a difficult situation is their confidence or courage.

example.ex: Something gave me the strength to overcome the difficulty...
example.tran: 有些事给了我克服困难的勇气。

example.ex: His strength is an inspiration to me in my life...
example.tran: 他的自信是对我人生的一种鼓舞。

example.ex: I think she showed great strength of character in turning down what must have been a very lucrative offer...
example.tran: 她拒绝了那个绝对诱人的提议，我认为这显示出了她性格中非凡的意志力。

example.ex: You need strength of mind to stand up for yourself.
example.tran: 你需要用精神力量来支持自己。

value.def: The strength of an object or material is its ability to be treated roughly, or to carry heavy weights, without being damaged or destroyed.

example.ex: He checked the strength of the cables.
example.tran: 他检查了一下钢索的强度。

example.ex: ...the properties of a material, such as strength or electrical conductivity.
example.tran: 一种材料的特性，比如强度或导电性

value.def: The strength of a person, organization, or country is the power or influence that they have.

example.ex: America values its economic leadership, and the political and military strength that goes with it...
example.tran: 美国重视其经济领导地位以及随之产生的政治和军事实力。

example.ex: The Alliance in its first show of strength drew a hundred thousand-strong crowd to a rally...
example.tran: 该联盟的第一次实力展示便吸引了 10 万余众参加集会。

example.ex: They have their own independence movement which is gathering strength.
example.tran: 他们自己发起了独立运动，其力量正逐渐壮大。

value.def: If you refer to the strength of a feeling, opinion, or belief, you are talking about how deeply it is felt or believed by people, or how much they are influenced by it.

example.ex: He was surprised at the strength of his own feeling...
example.tran: 他感情之强烈令他自己都很吃惊。

example.ex: ...the Civil War and the strength of feeling it had engendered among the Spanish people...
example.tran: 内战以及其在西班牙民众中所激发的强烈情感

example.ex: What makes a mayor successful in Los Angeles is the strength of his public support.
example.tran: 要想在洛杉矶当好市长，公众的大力支持是关键。

value.tran: (情感、意见、信念的)深度，强烈程度，影响程度

value.def: Someone's strengths are the qualities and abilities that they have which are an advantage to them, or which make them successful.

example.ex: Take into account your own strengths and weaknesses...
example.tran: 考虑一下你自己的优缺点。

example.ex: Vision and ambition are his great strengths...
example.tran: 目光远大、雄心勃勃是他的两大优点。

example.ex: Tact was never Mr Moore's strength...
example.tran: 摩尔先生处事不够圆通。

example.ex: Organisation is the strength of any good army...
example.tran: 任何优良部队都是很有组织纪律性的。

example.ex: The book's strength lay in its depiction of present-day Tokyo.
example.tran: 该书的精彩之处在于其对现今东京的描写。

value.def: If you refer to the strength of a currency, economy, or industry, you mean that its value or success is steady or increasing.

example.ex: ...the long-term competitive strength of the American economy...
example.tran: 美国经济的长期竞争力

example.ex: The drop was caused partly by the pound's strength against the dollar.
example.tran: 下降的部分原因在于英镑对美元的升值。

value.def: The strength of a group of people is the total number of people in it.

example.ex: ...elite forces, comprising about one-tenth of the strength of the army.
example.tran: 约占军队总人数1/10的精锐部队

value.def: The strength of a wind, current, or other force is its power or speed.

example.ex: Its oscillation depends on the strength of the gravitational field...
example.tran: 它的振动幅度取决于引力场的强度。

example.ex: A tropical storm is gaining strength in the eastern Atlantic.
example.tran: 在大西洋东部，一场热带风暴的风力正逐渐增强。

value.def: The strength of a drink, chemical, or drug is the amount of the particular substance in it that gives it its particular effect.

example.ex: It is very alcoholic, sometimes near the strength of port...
example.tran: 它的酒精浓度很高，有时接近波尔图葡萄酒的浓度。

example.ex: Each capsule contains between 30 and 100 pellets of morphine sulphate according to the strength of dose required...
example.tran: 根据所需剂量的浓度不同，每颗胶囊里含有 30 至 100 个吗啡硫酸盐颗粒。

example.ex: What's the scale that's used to compare the strength of acids and alkalis?
example.tran: 用何种标准来比较酸碱度？

value.tran: (饮料、化学品、药品的)浓度，浓淡程度

value.def: You can talk about the strength of a flavour, smell, colour, sound, or light to describe how intense or easily noticed it is.

example.ex: The wine has lots of strength of flavour.
example.tran: 该酒口味醇厚。

value.tran: (味道、气味、颜色、声音、光照的)程度

value.def: If a person or organization goes from strength to strength, they become more and more successful or confident.

example.ex: Since her heart and lung transplant operation she has gone from strength to strength...
example.tran: 做过心肺移植手术后，她的身体不断好转。

example.ex: A decade later, the company has gone from strength to strength.
example.tran: 十年后，该公司已经逐渐壮大。

value.tran: 日益兴隆;不断取得成功;信心倍增

value.def: If a team or army is at full strength, all the members that it needs or usually has are present.

example.ex: He needed more time to bring US forces there up to full strength.
example.tran: 他需要更多时间来增派兵力，以确保驻扎在那里的美国军队兵力充足。

example.ex: ...a full-strength team.
example.tran: 阵容齐整的队伍

gramarinfo.label: PHR after v, v-link PHR, PHR n

value.tran: (队伍或军队的)全员，满员，最佳阵容

value.def: If a group turns out in strength, they arrive in large numbers.

example.ex: Mr Gore called on voters and party workers to turn out in strength...
example.tran: 戈尔先生号召选民和政党工作人员积极前来投票。

example.ex: Security forces have been out in strength.
example.tran: 已经出动了大批安全部队。

value.def: If one thing is done on the strength of another, it is done because of the influence of that other thing.

example.ex: He was elected to power on the strength of his charisma...
example.tran: 他凭借其个人魅力而当选掌权。

example.ex: On the strength of those grades, he won a scholarship to Syracuse University.
example.tran: 凭借那些成绩，他赢得了锡拉丘兹大学的奖学金。

value.def: If an army or team is under strength or below strength, it does not have all the members that it needs or usually has.

example.ex: His regiments were considerably under strength...
example.tran: 他的几个团兵力严重不足。

example.ex: They had been beaten by a below-strength side.
example.tran: 他们被一支阵容不齐的队伍打败了。

gramarinfo.label: PHR after v, v-link PHR, PHR n

value.tran: (军队或队伍)人员不足，阵容不全
